Installation instructions for 20.04

Follow along this tutorial.
https://github.com/Daniil-Osokin/lightweight-human-pose-estimation-3d-demo.pytorch

Install python, cmake, opencv in system. also the part where you install vim for profile. 
https://linuxways.net/ubuntu/how-to-install-cuda-on-ubuntu-20-04/

create virtualenv. (python3 -m virtualenv lightweight-human-pose-estimation-3d-demo.pytorch
source lightweight-human-pose-estimation-3d-demo.pytorch/bin/activate)

grab the pretrained model.

to be able to run the demo (demo.py). go to the website below first
https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/

and then select stable (1.9), linux, pip, python and cuda 11.1. run the command through pip.

Run demo.py again and it should work.

Note: if you cannot get nvidia-smi to run, there is a need to disable secure boot on BIOS.
